Key Match Events: England finished top and Slovenia also advanced to the knockout stages of Euro 2024 after an uninspiring 0-0 draw in their final Group C match on Tuesday.
Trent Alexander-Arnold (England) missed a right footed shot from outside the box in the 90'+4' minute.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at RheinEnergieSTADION in Köln, Germany with an attendance of 41,536.
The match ended with England having 73.4% possession and Slovenia 26.6%.
England had 4 shots on goal compared to Slovenia's 1.
